# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Public brand configuration — SAFE TO COMMIT (no secrets here).
# Fill these in with the `/setup-project` command, or edit by hand.
# Left blank, the template ships unbranded and shows neutral placeholders.
#
# NOTE: these are Vite build-time vars — the dev server / build must
# reload to pick up changes (Vite restarts automatically on .env edits).
#
# Secrets (ADMIN_PASS / AUTH_PASS for the preview gate) do NOT belong here.
# Set those in Vercel's Environment Variables, or a local .env.local (ignored).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Company / organization name — shown in the dashboard header wordmark.
# Asked first by /setup-project. Falls back to VITE_CLIENT_NAME if left blank.
VITE_COMPANY_NAME=""

# Client name — the primary part of the title, e.g. the "ACME ltd" part.
VITE_CLIENT_NAME=""

# Project name — the secondary label, e.g. the "Refinements" part of the title.
VITE_PROJECT_NAME=""

# Fills the site tagline shown in the masthead/header. Optional.
VITE_SITE_TAGLINE=""

# ── Project type ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Drives the device-preview matrix (see previewConfig in src/config/site.ts).
# Asked by /setup-project. One of:
#   website — desktop + mobile baseline (tablet optional). DEFAULT when blank.
#   app     — mobile-first; the desktop preview is hidden (tablet optional).
#   brand   — Brand Guideline mode. Stubbed / coming soon: no dedicated preview
#             yet, so it currently behaves like "website".
VITE_PROJECT_TYPE=""

# Set to "true" to include a tablet preview button. Asked as a follow-up during
# /setup-project (websites and apps default to no tablet unless requested).
VITE_ENABLE_TABLET=""

# ── Phase II marker ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Set to "true" once the styleguide has been configured for this project
# (fonts & colors set in the token layer, example sections adapted). While
# blank/false, a setup banner shows on the styleguide page. See /setup-styleguide.
VITE_STYLEGUIDE_READY=""

# ── Brand palette marker (base scope) ────────────────────────
# Set to "true" once THIS project's brand palette has been established (via
# /setup-styleguide, which rewrites src/styles/brand.ts + the --ta-* tokens in
# tokens.css). While blank/false the styleguide flags its Colors as template
# defaults. Governs the BASE (v00) only — each variation carries its own
# `brandStatus` in its record. Only the project palette (--ta-*); never --admin-*.
VITE_BRAND_READY=""
